@people who have done summer SE internships: 

What was the best aspect(s) of your internship(s)? Was it the people, the product, the team, bonding with the other interns, or something else? Was there something unexpected that made you like (or dislike) an internship experience more than you anticipated? How important was location to you? 

I have a couple competing offers for my first (and last) internship and this is turning into a harder decision that I initially thought. I'm trying to hear more from past interns in general than the recruiters I've been talking with.

